<title>USA: Trichet sees further entry to ERM by year-end.</title>
<headline>Trichet sees further entry to ERM by year-end.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bank of France governor Jean-Claude Trichet said on Tuesday that another currency would probably enter the European Exchange Rate Mechanism (ERM) before the end of the year.</p>
<p>He had been asked in an interview with Reuters Financial Television in New York when he expected the Italian lira to rejoin the ERM.</p>
<p>&quot;The intention of the Italian authorities has been expressed publicly and I hope very much that we could have, when the time comes, the time will probably come before the end of the year, a further entry into the ERM and we will see through the appropriate procedures how to organise that,&quot; he said.</p>
<p>He declined to give further details.</p>
